ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a wonderful class that can teach you how to read in a new light. I have already recommended the course and the professor's work to several of my friends.
Interesting. Yes. It inspires students a lot.

I would highly recommend this course, but would emphasize its exploratory rather than canonical makeup. This is not a survey of different literary forms. It seeks out something much more nebulous and interesting, I think.
I would definitely recommend it to others.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course taught me how to read in a new light, and the true definition of close reading. It is not a stretch to say that this class has changed the way I approach texts and write about them.
The materials of this course broadened my vision and guided me to the wonderful world of philosophy. This course also taught me how to appreciate different forms of beauty.
I think the first section on Plato is the most helpful to deepen my knowledge of the discipline.
